caption: The bbq NZ lamb chops was a great reminder of lamb I’ve had in England and Yorkshire Pudding was made exactly how the British enjoy their Sunday Roasts. The salmon with the Dijon glaze was worthy of a round 2.  Cocktails were great and the service was even better. Recommend Hamilton’s on any occasion.

We haven't had a date since last March. My husband and I had a Valentine's day dinner without our children here tonight and it was magnificent. I felt transported back into the 1920s. We tried a margarita and an Irish coffee that were both excellent. Dinner was reasonably priced for the quality. If you go here and don't try the s'mores pie you're losing out!

We had one of the best group impromptu get togethers that I've ever had. We had a multitude of staff waiting in us from the host, waitstaff and bartenders.  I can say that we wanted for nothing that evening. The quality of the food was outstanding and prepared like what I would recieve in some of the high end restaurants in Chicago or elsewhere. I will definitely be back.

Was here in November and had a great experience. Food and drinks were fantastic, but service was even better. Our server and manager were both incredibly attentive to our small party of two! Will be ordering takeout here while our lockdown continues. Thank you again to the staff who made the visit so special!
The family meal was great! We got the seafood pasta which was delicious and with the salad the portions were generous for four people.

Outdoor seating in individual table clear “bubble” tents with heaters & ventilation feel safe from infection control perspective & all staff masked & only enter to serve/remove plates & drinks. They interact & chat from outside the tent. Added bonus is their already great food & service but having this safe winter friendly experience is incredible

This place was worth the experience, the time, and your money!! We called to reserve a spot and they squeezed us in at 7:45 when they close at 8. They did not rush us and the staff was professional. The food was excellent.

Probably the nicest, most upscale restaurant in all of CU. Staff always professional in all ways, dressed to the nines, always on time and orders are timed perfectly, ready when estimated, and neat to watch the meals all come together. Staff very polite to us drivers.  My best tips EVER have ALWAYS came from here. One of my parents' favorite places to eat, and the chefs come out and talk to their patrons, and even with masks on, they recognized them and all said hello, while giving away steak chili Mac to signal their reopening during Covid19 shutdown. They are happy to get their Patio Time back end of month!  Go support this fine dining establishment, keep our top quality restaurant around thru these shutdown periods, they could use your curbside, patio dining, or delivery services, as could us Grub Hub delivery drivers! We love this place, one and all!

First, make a reservation. They were kind enough to seat us even though we didn't have one. The service was top notch, even had 2 different managers check in on us. When asked by them how everything was, we couldn't be liars, we told them the food was great because it truly was one of the best tasting steaks. Best part about the steaks is HW does NOT put any seasoning on their steaks. That tells me they don't want to ruin a great piece of meat. And might I suggest getting the spinach salad. Of course raw spinach tastes different than boiled, but there's a bacon dressing HW puts on it that's too good. Then there's boiled eggs, mushrooms, small pieces of onion, slices of radishes, croutons, and I'm sure I've missed more of the salad, but I could have had a whole meal just from that. We also ordered 2 sides. The green beans were excellent, they covered in some sort of garlic sauce. The other was the lobster mac and cheese, which wasn't the best I've ever had. It didn't seem to have enough lobster and the mac was bland. But to end on a positive note,  I'll say the bread that was brought to the table was also good, giving 3 choices of butter, a salted, an herb, and sweet butter that gets rotated out. On our visit it was a pumpkin spice, which I thought was pretty good. But overall, definitely worth every piece of 5 stars.

SUPERB HIGHLY RECOMMEND BEST RESTAURANT SERVICE I HAVE RECEIVED IN THE WHOLE STATE OF ILLINOIS SINCE I MOVED FROM NEW YORK 100 STARS!!! OH AND MIGHT I ADD DIANE THE OWNER VERY POLITE AND FRIENDLY AND KENDRA THE WAITRESS STAFF VERY FRIENDLY AND POLITE THEY BOTH WENT ABOVE AND BEYOND TO MAKE SURE MY ORDER WAS PERFECT!! I WILL BE BACK AGAIN!!!

This place is fantastic.
Very nice place to take your family to!  Excellent management and employees!
Great food and service.
Excellent service. Wonderful food!

Hamilton Walkers served my family a fabulous dinner recently.  We ordered a variety of entrees and everything was delicious, from the steaks to the seafood to the side dishes.  The service was also wonderful.  Both the manager and the chef came to our table to make sure everything was to our satisfaction.  We visited during phase 4 of the Illinois COVID-19 recovery plan so the staff wore masks for safety.  I was impressed that EVERYONE took this seriously, meaning the masks were worn properly to cover both mouth and nose, not just hanging below the face for show!  This restaurant is a jewel in our community, providing a top level dining experience you might seek in Chicago or other large cities, and very affordable in comparison.
Open for indoor seating! Food is always delicious!
Relaxing atmosphere with fantastic food and great service!
Amazing, as always!

Great steakhouse. Everything is always fantastic. I travel for work and have been to many of the best steakhouses in Vegas and all over the country and to me, Hamilton Walker’s is right up there with the quality, atmosphere, and service; and it ends up a better bang for your buck than you’ll find anywhere on the LV Strip. Also the grilled lobster was some of the best lobster I had in recent memory.

i am sure its one of the nicer places in town, it seemed pricy compared to a ruth chris which i would give 5 stars.  service was nice and the multi grain bread was very unique.

Had an amazing dinner.  The prime rib and white fish were great.  Rory was our server and he was super.  Very attentive.  We were trying to take a selfie by their sign and a guy came by and asked us if he could take it.  Sure!  He took a great picture and it turns out he is the Chef - Zach.  VERY nice and friendly guy.  And it wasn't even Valentine's Day.  The chocolate marshmallow butter is to die for.  I wish they sold it.  Everyone at the front desk was super too.

We went Sunday around 1215 and didn't get our food for an hour and a half. Nothing we ordered should have taken long to make, the 6oz. filet would have been the longest. The service was abhorrent then our waiter brought my daughter a birthday dessert which no one asked for. I guess my naivety got the best of me because I assumed this was a type of apology for the two hours that we had been there. That was not the case as the dessert appeared on my bill. It stated: special occasion dessert.........$7.99. Needless to say this was my family and friends first and last time we will ever occasion Hamilton Walker's. As far as I can tell the entry sign is the best part of this restaurant.

This was our first visit.  We went at happy hour (3-6 pm) and sat at the bar.  I had a wonderful Sazarac, and our bartender Damian, in response to my request, instructed my husband in how to make one at home.  We made an early dinner from a half price appetizer, the heritage tomato tower with lamb "lollichops" individually priced at $2.50 each.  We were early so the staff had time for some pleasant conversation and we have planned to make this a weekly event for the next month or two.

Awesome food. great cuts and seafood.  Prime rib was awesome. Oysters were sources from river and incredible.

We visited HW for our first dinner  out in 2020 celebrating Lisa's birthday.  We arrived a little early, were able to be seated but chose an aperitif at the bar. I ordered a Sazerac out of curiosity, Lisa chose a select Kentucky Bourbon.  Both drinks were excellent and bartenders knowledgeable in their craft. Once seated, we ordered; fish, fillet mignon, 3 side vegetables and baked goat cheese w/roasted pepper with toasted bread as an appetizer. Lisa's fish was light delicate flavorful, my aged fillet was melt in your mouth tender. The vegetables were roasted, cooked yet crisp. This meal was by far one of the best meals we have had in the past 10 years. I enjoyed the surroundings, staff was attentive, if not a little stiff. Be aware, HW is a great dining experience, yet be prepared to pay for excellence. One star deducted for charging me for anchovies on my Caesar  salad.
Great lunch experience.  Was able to order off the dinner menu! Everything was top notch, as was our sever, Cara! I would highly recommend to anyone.
Good food cooked to perfection.  My friends and I had lunch: steak cooked exactly as each of us ordered and crisp, tasty green beans. I always order medium and this was done right.

My family and I had a reservation for Sunday at 7pm. We were assured by the staff (we called ahead) that they were not busy. We arrived hungry and with high hopes. It took 1.5 Hours for us to be served our soup and salad, as we watched those who came in after us being served theirs and some even their entrees. It wasn’t until after we received our soup that a manager came to speak with us and simply giggled and said “Well, I hope the rest of your food is delicious”. She then left and attended to other customers multiple times throughout the night, disregarding us. While our meals had already included dessert, their only offer to compensate for their service was more free dessert. We were overwhelmed with dessert and underwhelmed with the service. Overall would not recommend. While our server was great, the kitchen and other staff were unprepared. As a restaurant with steep prices, they should’ve been better prepared on a fairly slow business night.

Champaign was a great town to visit and Hamilton Walker's was the best place we ate all week. I want to say beef is what they do best but everything we had here was top notch. From the cocktails all the way through to dessert. The service was above expectation and the server was very knowledgable when asked questions about menu items. Highly recommended for anyone you're looking to impress from a business dinner to something romantic, they won't let you down.

Save your money and time. Painfully slow service for a Sunday brunch.  Food is hit and miss, mostly miss.  The prime rib hash should be relabeled “plate of potatoes with cheese and a few dried out pieces of meat, served warm after sitting under a light for a while hash”.  Omelette served without advertised sides/ingredients. Not a huge deal if it hadn’t cost $18.  Creme brûlée comes with complimentary hair, if that’s your thing then definitely dig in. Looking at previous comments leads me to believe that someone there has a thing for putting hair in food.  The pancakes are big pieces of oversized goodness. I would eat these again. The hair issue has made me cautious though.  Management “cared” but not enough to make it right. No discounts, nothing, just a “hope to see you back” and a removal of the hairy creme brûlée from the bill.  Again, save your money and time and go up the street a bit to Watson’s, Destihl, Big Grove Tavern, etc.

Great ambiance and customer service.....would have given 5 but the servers were missing a few details, especially being a slow night @ 25% capacity. I will return to tune again.
Great food!  Great service!!  Definitely worth the money,  will definitely be back!! ❤

Firstly, props for this restaurant taking OpenTable reservations. This was truly a pleasant find. A touch more expensive than perhaps Google Maps let on, but you pay for rich, quality food. The establishment is not large, but doesn't feel tight. If there is a lull in the conversation, Big Band music can be heard unobtrusively in the background, however most of the Saturday night, the room was filled with laughter & genuine conversations. Surprisingly, I was probably on my phone the most (taking pictures of the food & writing this review), but others were thoroughly enjoying each other's conversations & presence. And I had a nearly equally  good time, delighting in the food, taking in a contemplative solitary supper & observing others. What a gem; I'll certainly return.

The food and drinks are always top notch. Service is generally good but, during our last visit, our server appeared disheveled and seemed distracted or preoccupied. We had to ask for our table bread from another service during the wait between our appetizer and our mains.

Good service. Had a very delicious ribeye cooked to perfection. The twice baked potato was dry and nearly tasteless. We had it before and it was much better, not sure what happened this time. Hamilton Walker’s is in a great location, has a nice atmosphere, and some dishes are worth going back for. I recently had the rack of lamb which was very well prepared (I did have to add salt), the crab cake (tasty and would get again), and the heirloom tomato tower (interesting dish that I would like to try again when tomatoes are actually in season). The prime rib, while prepared well, was under seasoned. I have had a few of their blue plate specials for lunch and these have always been great meals at a very reasonable price. The service I have never been impressed by, typically a bit slow with the entrees. Overall this is a good place to eat lunch and, if you want to have the Chicago steak experience, then dinner as well. It is definitely pricey (besides their blue plate specials) and I find that their sides and non-steak items are generally the best parts of the meal.

The drinks from the bar were perfect. Service was great. Food was cooked to perfection.
excellent service. excellent atmosphere, food  very good with excellent menu

Food was just OK...overpriced in my opinion for what you get. Service has left something to be desired each of the three times I've been I LOVE Nando across the street- go there instead - for Italian and great value

This was arguably one of the worst steak restaurants that I have ever been to.  I started the meal with an order of Oysters Rockefeller.  After eating a couple, my girlfriend literally spit out a bite.  After trying some of the oyster that that came from it literally tasted rotten.  Then, our steaks came out and I ordered a filet, my girlfriends, a rib-eye.  My filet was completely under cooked in the middle and charred black on the outside.  I am a fan or medium rare meat but this was nearly raw on the inside.  I am not one who likes to send food back but I had to since I didn't want raw beef.  After it came back, It was even more charred on the outside to the point were the only taste I could notice was the one of burnt carbon.  Not to mention that they barely cooked it much more on the inside.  My girlfriend's rib-eye was sub-par.  It was a very thin cut, which does not leave any room to keep the center medium rare or get a good sear on the outside.  The only thing that was ok about the meal was the lobster tail I ordered on the side with my steak (which in all honesty is one of the easiest things to cook without messing it up).  I also failed to mention that the prices there were absurd.  For what was nearly a $150-200 meal for two, which was supposed to be a celebratory meal, this was absolutely THE MOST disappointing dining experience I have had in a long time, possibly ever.  I would never recommend this place to anyone and will certainly never go back under any circumstance.
